{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OmniLight3D\/omniAttenuation","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot11OmniLight3DC15omniAttenuationSdvp","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"symbolKind":"property","roleHeading":"Instance Property","title":"omniAttenuation","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"omniAttenuation"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Double","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd"}]},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OmniLight3D"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/omnilight3d\/omniattenuation"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Controls the distance attenuation function for omnilights."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"omniAttenuation"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Double"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A value of ","type":"text"},{"code":"0.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will maintain a constant brightness through most of the range, but smoothly attenuate the light at the edge of the range. Use a value of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"2.0"},{"type":"text","text":" for physically accurate lights as it results in the proper inverse square attenutation."}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Setting attenuation to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"2.0"},{"type":"text","text":" or higher may result in distant objects receiving minimal light, even within range. For example, with a range of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"4096"},{"type":"text","text":", an object at "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"100"},{"type":"text","text":" units is attenuated by a factor of "},{"code":"0.0001","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". With a default brightness of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1"},{"type":"text","text":", the light would not be visible at that distance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note"},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using negative or values higher than "},{"code":"10.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" may lead to unexpected results."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note"}]}],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/OmniLight3D/omniAttenuation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OmniLight3D\/omniAttenuation","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/omnilight3d\/omniattenuation","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"omniAttenuation"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","text":"Double","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Controls the distance attenuation function for omnilights.","type":"text"}],"title":"omniAttenuation","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","title":"SwiftGodot","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/OmniLight3D":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OmniLight3D","title":"OmniLight3D","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/omnilight3d","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OmniLight3D","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OmniLight3D","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Omnidirectional light, such as a light bulb or a candle.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol"}}}